# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# There are no API keys here on purpose. Anything prefixed VITE_ is inlined into
# the public JavaScript bundle at build time, which means it is readable by
# anyone who opens DevTools. A key in this file would not be a secret.
#
# The real keys live as Cloudflare Worker secrets (see worker/README.md):
#   cd worker
#   npx wrangler secret put GEMINI_API_KEY
#   npx wrangler secret put GROQ_API_KEY

# URL of your deployed API proxy Worker. Public, not a secret — it's protected
# by the Worker's origin allowlist and per-IP rate limit, not by obscurity.
# Leave blank to build a bring-your-own-key-only app.
#
# You'll get this URL from `npx wrangler deploy` — it looks like
# https://clip-web-api.<your-cloudflare-subdomain>.workers.dev
VITE_API_PROXY_URL=
